  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nJelly-O Pop\nFood Info\n12.5\n20\n0\nMeat\nObject Info\nPerk\nLowers temperature by 40 degrees for 10 seconds\n3 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1 x1 x1 x1\nx1 x1 x1 x1\n10 sec\n20\nMiscellaneous\n\"jellyopop\"\n“Jelly-O pop it right in my mouth!”\n–Wilson\n“I want twenty!”\n–Willow\n“Looks like candy, but tastes like meat!”\n–Wolfgang\n“Death comes to us all. Sometimes on a stick.”\n–Wendy\n“IT WILL KEEP MY SYSTEMS RUNNING”\n–WX-78\n“Takes me back to my youth. Sort of.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“I guess this is a dessert island, eh?”\n–Woodie\n“Hm... I don't think this meshes well with my cultivated look.”\n–Maxwell\n“Strangely enough, this does not cause me stomach upset.”\n–Wagstaff\n“I cöuld gö berserk ön these!”\n–Wigfrid\n“Yummy!”\n–Webber\n“Is this junk food or health food? I can't tell.”\n–Walani\n“Hmmm... An interesting flavor.”\n–Warly\n“Woodlegs' specialty!”\n–Woodlegs\n“'TIS NUMS O' CHEWY FISHIES”\n–Wilba\n“Cold Glub Glub Blob”\n–Wormwood\n“Looks... delicious?”\n–Wheeler\nJelly-O Pop is a Crock Pot dish exclusive in the Shipwrecked DLC. It is made from any form of Jellyfish (Dead/Cooked Jellyfish and Dried Jellyfish), 1 Ice and 1 Inedible.\nAdding a Wobster will yield Lobster Bisque instead. Adding an extra 1.0 unit of fish may yield Ceviche instead. Adding Shark Fin may yield Shark Fin Soup instead. Despite Jellyfish being a Monster Food, adding another Monster Food like Monster Meat will not yield Monster Lasagna because the Crock Pot Priority of this recipe is higher than Monster Lasagna.\nIt restores 20 and 12.5 , and reduces body temperature by 1 degree per second for 10 seconds. Jelly-O Pop is similar to Banana Pop, but without the Sanity gain.\nRecipes[edit | edit source]\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×2\n33% chance to result in Shark Fin Soup.\n33% chance to result in Ceviche.\nExchange[edit | edit source]\nTips[edit | edit source]\nCooked Jellyfish restores more hunger than Jelly-O-Pop, however it restores half the health. Therefore this recipe is more useful for healing, but eating the Jellyfish directly after cooking is more useful for hunger.\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
