  "summaryViHtml": "<h2>Tóm tắt</h2><p>Jelly-O Pop là món Nồi Hầm độc quyền trong DLC ​​Shipwrecked. Nó được làm từ bất kỳ dạng Sứa nào (Sứa chết/Nấu chín và Sứa khô), 1 Đá và 1 Không ăn được.</p>",
  "title": "Jelly-O Pop",
  "wikitext": "{{Exclusivity|Shipwrecked}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|icon = Jelly-O Pop.png\n|image = Jelly-O Pop Dropped.png\n|canBeBurned=1\n|foodRecipe = {{Pic|32px|Jellyfish}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Ice}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Inedible}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Filler}}x1<hr>{{Pic|32px|Dead Jellyfishes}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Ice}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Inedible}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Filler}}x1\n|foodType = [[Food Type#Meat|Meat]] {{Pic|32px|Meats|Food Type#Meat}}\n|crafting       = Cooked in a [[Crock Pot]]\n|hpRestored     = 20\n|hungerRestored = 12.5\n|sanityRestored = 0\n|cooktime       = 10 sec\n|priority       = 20\n|spoil          = 3 Days\n|perk           = Lowers temperature by 40 degrees for 10 seconds\n|stack          = 40\n|spawnCode      = \"jellyopop\"\n}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = Jelly-O pop it right in my mouth!\n|willow = I want twenty!\n|wolfgang = Looks like candy, but tastes like meat!\n|wendy = Death comes to us all. Sometimes on a stick.\n|wx78 = IT WILL KEEP MY SYSTEMS RUNNING\n|wickerbottom = Takes me back to my youth. Sort of.\n|woodie = I guess this is a dessert island, eh?\n|maxwell = Hm... I don't think this meshes well with my cultivated look.\n|wagstaff = Strangely enough, this does not cause me stomach upset.\n|wigfrid = I cöuld gö berserk ön these!\n|webber = Yummy!\n|walani = Is this junk food or health food? I can't tell.\n|warly = Hmmm... An interesting flavor.\n|woodlegs = Woodlegs' specialty!\n|wilba = 'TIS NUMS O' CHEWY FISHIES\n|wormwood = Cold Glub Glub Blob\n|wheeler = Looks... delicious?\n|choose = wickerbottom\n}}\n\n'''Jelly-O Pop''' is a [[Crock Pot]] dish exclusive in the ''[[Shipwrecked]]'' DLC. It is made from any form of [[Jellyfish]] ([[Dead Jellyfish|Dead/Cooked Jellyfish]] and [[Dried Jellyfish]]), 1 [[Ice]] and 1 [[Inedibles|Inedible]].\n\nAdding a [[Wobster]] will yield [[Lobster Bisque]] instead. Adding an extra 1.0 unit of [[Fishes|fish]] may yield [[Ceviche]] instead. Adding [[Shark Fin]] may yield [[Shark Fin Soup]] instead. Despite Jellyfish being a [[Monster Food]], adding another Monster Food like [[Monster Meat]] will not yield [[Monster Lasagna]] because the [[Crock Pot#Priority|Crock Pot Priority]] of this recipe is higher than Monster Lasagna.\n\nIt restores 20 {{Hp}} and 12.5 {{Hunger}}, and reduces body temperature by 1 degree per second for 10 seconds. Jelly-O Pop is similar to [[Banana Pop]], but without the [[Sanity]] gain.\n\n== {{Pic32|Cookbook}} Recipes ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Jellyfish\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Inedible\n|item4 = Filler\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Jelly-O Pop\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Dead Jellyfishes\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Inedible\n|item4 = Filler\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Jelly-O Pop\n}}\n\n== {{Pic32|Crock Pot}} Examples ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Jellyfish\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Twigs\n|item4 = Seaweed\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Jelly-O Pop\n}}{{Recipe\n|item1 = Dried Jellyfish\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Twigs\n|item4 = \n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Jelly-O Pop\n|count3 = 2\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Dead Jellyfish\n|item2 = Ice\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Dorsal Fin\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Jelly-O Pop\n}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Cooked Jellyfish\n|item2 = Ice\n|item3 = Twigs\n|item4 = Shark Fin\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Jelly-O Pop\n|note = 33% chance to result in [[Shark Fin Soup]].<br/> 33% chance to result in [[Ceviche]].\n}}\n\n== {{Pic32|Dubloons}} Exchange ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Jelly-O Pop\n|tool = Yaarctopus Icon\n|result = Sea Trap\n}}\n\n== {{pic32|Prototype}}Tips ==\n*Cooked Jellyfish restores more hunger than Jelly-O-Pop, however it restores half the health. Therefore this recipe is more useful for healing, but eating the Jellyfish directly after cooking is more useful for hunger.\n\n{{Crock Pot Food}}\n__NOTOC__[[fr:sucette de méduse]]\n[[Category:Food]]\n[[Category:Perishables]]\n[[Category:Healing]]\n[[Category:Cooling]]\n[[Category:Crock Pot Recipes]]\n[[Category:Non-Flammable]]"
}
